📘 Legal Calculus — Module 08

Numbered Facts Beat Rhetoric

⚖️ Core Message

Facts win when they’re easy to cite. Short, numbered, supported, and neutral in tone.
📖 Lesson Content

1. One fact per paragraph; cite exhibit and page.
2. Avoid argument words inside the fact section.
3. Use a separate 'Argument' or 'Request' section after the facts.
4. Cross‑reference a timeline for speed.
📝 Assignment

Write 10 numbered facts with exhibit cites (Ex. A at 2; Ex. B at 1) and a short request section.
✅ Model Response

FACTS

1. On July 21, 2025, Plaintiff filed an emergency motion (Ex. A at 2).

2. USPS delivered to the Clerk on July 31, 2025 (Ex. B at 1).

REQUEST

Plaintiff requests the Court set a 20‑minute hearing on irreparable harm.

 

💡 Reflection Summary

Let the reader verify each fact in one step.
🎨 Visual Concept

A checklist with short numbered lines and exhibit icons.
